column10:
The New Balance 1906R Silver Black leans into Y2K trends with a striking colorway of metallic silver, black, and white.

Featuring a low-top, lace-up design inspired by sneakers from the early 2000s, this version of the 1906R boasts a white mesh base with black accents on the heel, sock liner, rubber outsole, and ribbons threading through the signature New Balance N logo. However, the shiny silver overlays crisscrossing the upper stand out the most. The ABZORB SBS heel increases stability, while the ABZORB midsole protects against impact stress. Finally, the N-ergy technology in the outsole adds superior shock absorption as the Stability Web supports the midfoot arch.

Our experts at StockX like the classic New Balance 1906R branding, including "1906R" on the overlays, "NB RUNNING" on the tongue, and "NB" on the heel. The New Balance 1906R Silver Black was released on June 1, 2024, and sold for $155.

The Nike Vomero 5 Triple Black is part of Nike’s Vomero 5 lineup, which includes sneakers with a technical silhouette and a variety of function-first details.

The "Triple Black" comes with an all-black, mesh base and leather overlays. Like other editions of the Vomero 5, the sneaker features motifs of Bill Bowerman, a famous University of Oregon coach, on the insole. 3M reflective detailing along the overlays provides extra visibility during low lighting, while Zoom Air cushioning adds comfort and support. The sneaker’s all-black colorway makes it stand out from other versions of the Vomero 5 and gives the shoe a sleek appearance.

Something our experts love is the plastic heel counter. It features a grid-like design and complements the plastic paneling on the side of the sneaker. The Nike Vomero 5 Triple Black was released on July 20, 2023, and retailed at $160.

column2: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Canary (Women's)
column10:
Immerse yourself in the stylish and bold world of the Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Canary (Women's), a sneaker that brings a fresh vibe to a classic silhouette. This edition is splashed in Canary, Racer Blue, and Light Silver hues, embodying the energy of Travis Scott's alma mater, Elkins High School. The sneaker’s design is highlighted by the iconic reversed Swoosh, a hallmark of Travis Scott’s transformative touch to the Jordan 1 & sneaker culture. Adorned with the Cactus Jack logo, these sneakers are a true testament to the rapper's influence and aesthetic.

The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Canary is a piece of wearable art. Crafted with premium materials for comfort and durability, the design also features a gum medium brown outsole that complements the vibrant upper, ensuring these shoes stand out in any crowd. The combination of Travis Scott's unique style and Jordan Brand's legendary craftsmanship offers wearers a mix of street-worthy appeal and high-fashion sensibility.

Released on May 17, 2024, the Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Canary (Women's) was retailed for $150. Each pair reflects the spirit of innovation and youth, capturing the essence of Travis Scott's creative vision and the enduring legacy of the Jordan brand. With each step, wearers celebrate a legacy of musical prowess and sneaker history, making it a coveted addition to any collection.

The adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Salt, Influenced by military and utility design, was made available as part of Season 7 lineup collection.

This version was made of breathable mesh, suede, and nubuck with a Salt color palette. Its disassembled design lines are reminiscent of the 500 sneakers. Rubber outsoles are .finished in complementary colors. A 3M fluorescent nylon pull tab runs the entire length of the tongue's spine. A thick foam midsole with EVA cushioning and a serrated rubber outsole, both of which take on tonal colors dependent on the upper, complete the overall design.

The adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Salt first debuted on 14 September 2019 and retailed at $200.

column2: Jordan Jumpman Jack TR Travis Scott Dark Mocha
column10:
The Air Jordan Jumpman Jack TR Travis Scott Dark Mocha, also known as the Jordan CJ1 T-Rexx, is the third colorway of Travis Scott's signature sneaker model, the Jumpman Jack.

This Dark Mocha colorway features and all black and brown design with a velcro tongue flap, reverse swoosh branding, and the Air Jordan logo on the tongue. The underside of the sneaker also showcases unique Cactus Jack branding. This colorway is by far the most neutral and muted colorway of the Jumpman Jack so far, making it a versatile sneaker for many different occasion. As Travis Scott continues to ascend to new heights, his sneakers and surely set to become as hot as ever.

The Air Jordan Jumpman Jack TR Travis Scott Dark Mocha released on November 26th, 2024, for a retail price of $200. We love this sneaker due to it's iconic Cactus Jack branding and recognizable style in the world of sneakers.

Please Note: Dust bag is not required

For the first time in over a decade, the Air Jordan 4 Retro Thunder is returning and is being featured as part of the Jordan Brand Spring/Summer 2023 campaign.

Jordan Brand brought back this fan favorite colorway that is constructed using premium black nubuck uppers with splashes of Tour Yellow throughout the midsole, lace eyelets, and tongue. Michael Jordan's iconic Jumpman logo is placed on the heel tab, tongue and insoles of the sneakers.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro Thunder (2023) released May 13, 2023, with a retail price of $210.

The ASICS Gel-1130 White Aqua (GS) presents the Gel-1130 in a kids’ size. This technical running shoe boasts performance-enhancing technologies and a colorway of crisp white and aqua.

The upper construction features breathable mesh in white with a slightly loose weave. Aqua accents add splashes of color on the tongue branding, plastic pieces on the midsole, and along the upper. Like running sneakers in the ASICS catalog from the early 2000s, this shoe displays synthetic overlays with black and metallic silver stripes. In terms of technology, gel units in the midsole provide supportive cushioning and protect against impact stress. Padding around the collar and in the tongue contributes to the sneaker’s bulky, Y2K aesthetic.

Our StockX experts like the metallic silver mudguard that protects the toe area and carries a hint of aqua. The grade school–sized ASICS Gel-1130 White Aqua (GS) was originally released on March 3, 2024, and sold for $85.

The New Balance 9060 Sea Salt Raincloud is a stylish and comfortable sneaker that combines modern design with classic New Balance aesthetics. Featuring a sleek silhouette, this shoe showcases a harmonious blend of sea salt and raincloud hues, creating a versatile and eye-catching look. The upper is crafted with premium materials, ensuring durability and breathability for all-day wear. The innovative ABZORB midsole technology provides superior cushioning and support, making these sneakers perfect for both casual outings and active lifestyles. Designed with attention to detail, the New Balance 9060 Sea Salt Raincloud boasts a chunky sole that adds a contemporary edge to its overall appearance. The shoe's construction incorporates a mix of suede and mesh panels, offering a luxurious feel and enhanced ventilation. The iconic 'N' logo is prominently displayed on the side, paying homage to the brand's heritage while embracing modern sneaker trends. With its balanced combination of style and functionality, this New Balance model is set to become a staple in any sneaker enthusiast's collection. Us at StockX believe this product is great for those seeking a versatile sneaker that effortlessly transitions from casual wear to light athletic activities, offering both comfort and style in one package.

column2: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro White Gum
column10:
Nike SB is launching into 2023 with the release of the Nike SB Dunk Gum Pack. Nike’s Gum Pack features the Nike SB Dunk Low Pro in White Gum and Black Gum colorways.

The Nike Sb Dunk Low Pro White Gum is constructed using premium tumbled leather across the uppers, and black nubuck swooshes. The sneakers sit on top of a gum colored outsole, and feature black Nike branding on the heel, tongue, and insoles.
The Nike SB Dunk Low Pro White Gum released March 1, 2023, with a retail price of $110.

Jordan is going back to the classics in 2023, releasing a special edition Air Jordan 1 Low in the popular black and white Concord colorway.

The Jordan 1 Low SE Concord’s draw inspiration from the Air Jordan 11 Concord, highlighted by the sneakers combination of black patent leather, and white leather uppers. Jordan brand used a translucent blue outsole, and added a white Air Jordan Wings logo placed on the heel of each sneaker.

The Air Jordan 1 Low SE Concord released January 17, 2023, with a retail price of $120.

The Jordan 3 Retro Black Cat (2025) (GS) is a sleek and stylish sneaker designed for the younger generation. This Grade School edition showcases a monochromatic black colorway that pays homage to the iconic 'Black Cat' nickname of Michael Jordan. The upper is crafted with premium materials, featuring a combination of smooth and tumbled leather for a luxurious look and feel. The signature elephant print detailing on the toe and heel adds a classic touch to this modern iteration.

Comfort and performance are at the forefront of this design. The visible Air unit in the heel provides responsive cushioning, while the padded collar ensures a snug and supportive fit. The rubber outsole offers excellent traction, making these sneakers suitable for both casual wear and light athletic activities. Our experts state this product is great for young sneaker enthusiasts looking for a versatile and timeless shoe that combines style and functionality.

column2: Jordan 5 Retro OG Black Metallic Reimagined (GS)
column10:
The Jordan 5 Retro OG Black Metallic Reimagined (GS) brings one of Jordan Brand’s most legendary sneakers to a new generation of sneakerheads. Originally debuting in 1990, the Black Metallic colorway is a staple in the Air Jordan lineup, and this Reimagined edition stays true to its heritage while adding subtle modern refinements. Built for kids who want to step into sneaker history, this GS version features a sleek black nubuck upper, a reflective metallic silver tongue, and bold fire red Jumpman branding, delivering the same iconic look in a size made for smaller feet.

Designed with both style and comfort in mind, this pair includes metallic silver shark teeth on the midsole, translucent netting, and a visible Air unit in the heel—elements that have defined the AJ5 for over three decades. The 3M reflective tongue catches the light with every step, while nostalgic details like the Nike Air branding on the heel and the upside-down Air Jordan text on the tongue pay tribute to the OG design. Whether rocking them on the playground or the pavement, these kicks bring a piece of sneaker history to a new audience.

Released on March 2, 2025, for a retail price of $160, the Jordan 5 Retro OG Black Metallic Reimagined (GS) continues the legacy of one of the most celebrated Air Jordan 5 colorways. As part of Jordan Brand’s 35th anniversary Reimagined lineup, this kids’ version ensures the next generation can lace up a true classic.

column2: Nike SB Dunk Low The Wizard of Oz Poppy Field
column10:
The Nike SB Dunk Low The Wizard of Oz Poppy Field is a stunning homage to the timeless 1939 classic The Wizard of Oz. Inspired by the iconic poppy field scene where Dorothy and her friends fall under its magical spell, this sneaker transforms vivid storytelling into wearable art. Its unique design features a special print showcasing a floral tapestry of orange, red, yellow, green, and black, bringing the vibrant poppy field to life.

True to Nike SB’s legacy, the Poppy Field Dunk Low blends nostalgic details with contemporary craftsmanship. The heel features Dorothy’s legendary line, "There’s no place like home," embroidered in bold lettering. A second hidden layer of red leather peeks through the upper for added depth, while custom insoles include an image of the Wicked Witch of the West, making these sneakers a collector’s dream. Satin finishes, a lush red outsole, and the iconic "Wizard of Oz" text on the tongue complete the story-driven design.

Set to release on December 23, 2024, the Nike SB Dunk Low The Wizard of Oz Poppy Field will retail for $135. Whether you’re a sneaker enthusiast or a fan of the beloved film, this pair masterfully merges cinematic nostalgia with modern skate culture, offering a wearable tribute to Dorothy’s unforgettable journey.

Disclaimer: All blind bags must be opened in order to verify the shoes inside

The Jordan Spizike Low Black Cat continues the legacy of Michael Jordan and director Spike Lee’s partnership by applying an all-black colorway to the Air Jordan Spizike Low.

This shoe pays homage to Lee’s contributions to film history and the iconic triple-black "Black Cat" colorway, known for its sleek, stealthy look. Taking elements from previous Air Jordan sneakers, including the Air Jordan 3, 4, 5, and 6, this version of the Spizike boasts soft cushioning in the tongue and collar. Velvety nubuck deepens the black’s rich hue, while the mudguard is crafted from suede and the heel and toe overlays display the signature elephant print.

Our experts like the way the all-black aesthetic reaches the shiny midsole and durable rubber outsole. In addition, visible air units in the heel complete the look and speak to the sneaker’s Jordan-brand heritage. The Jordan Spizike Low Black Cat was released on June 11, 2024, and sold for $160.

The Nike Air Foamposite One Galaxy (2025) revives one of the most legendary sneaker releases of all time. Originally launching in 2012 as part of Nike Basketball’s All-Star "Galaxy Pack," the Foamposite quickly became a cultural icon, sparking massive hype and even chaotic release-day stories. More than just a sneaker, the "Galaxy" Foamposite represented the intensity of sneaker culture, and now, in 2025, it's making its highly anticipated return. The futuristic obsidian and black Foamposite shell serves as a base, allowing the cosmic theme to take center stage, while anthracite accents complete the sleek aesthetic.

Just like its predecessor, the 2025 edition retains the signature glow-in-the-dark outsole, adding to its out-of-this-world appeal. Details like the "Remove Before Flight" pull tabs and Penny Hardaway’s 1 Cent logo remain intact, staying true to the original design that captivated sneakerheads over a decade ago. This drop isn’t just another rerelease—it’s a revival of one of the most sought-after sneakers in history.

Landing on February 21, 2025, the Nike Air Foamposite One Galaxy (2025) retailed at $230, bringing back the magic of the original with a fresh perspective. Dressed in obsidian, black, and anthracite, this pair is a must-have for collectors and those looking to own a piece of sneaker history.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro White Thunder (GS) is a striking new release that pays homage to one of the most iconic colorways in Jordan Brand history. Inspired by the original Black and Yellow Thunder 4s, this grade school version brings a fresh take to the classic design. The upper features a predominantly black nubuck material, providing a sleek and bold look, while white accents create a sharp contrast. The Jumpman logo appears on both the tongue’s flight patch and the heel, ensuring that this sneaker remains true to its roots while introducing a new visual twist.

The Air Jordan 4 holds a special place in the world of basketball sneakers, originally released in 1989 as the first Jordan model to be released globally. Its unique design elements, such as the plastic wings and mesh netting, set it apart from its predecessors and have made it a fan favorite over the years. The White Thunder colorway continues this legacy by offering a fresh take on the silhouette that captures the essence of the original while adding a modern touch.

Released on August 24, 2024, the Air Jordan 4 Retro White Thunder (GS) retailed at $160. The black, white, and black colorway provides a striking contrast that makes this sneaker stand out in any collection. This grade school release ensures that even younger fans of the Jordan brand can step out in style with a piece of basketball history.

The Nike KD 4 Aunt Pearl (2024) is a re-release of one of the most beloved colorways in the KD 4 series. Paying tribute to Kevin Durant’s late Aunt Pearl, this sneaker features a striking pinkfire 2 colorway with black and metallic silver accents. Beyond its eye-catching design, the Aunt Pearl edition holds deep sentimental value, honoring Durant's aunt who passed away from cancer. The pink hue symbolizes strength and hope, making this sneaker a tribute to those fighting the battle against cancer.

The Aunt Pearl originally debuted as part of Nike’s efforts to raise cancer awareness, and its re-release brings back all the emotional and cultural impact it had on the sneaker world. The pink colorway stands out, while the details like the metallic silver swoosh and unique KD branding remind fans why this is one of the most sought-after KD sneakers ever released.

Released on October 3, 2024, the Nike KD 4 Aunt Pearl (2024) retailed for $130. This re-release brings back all the emotional weight and iconic design that made the original Aunt Pearl KD 4 so special, making it a must-cop for sneakerheads.

Introducing the Air Jordan 11 Retro Low 'Space Jam', an iconic silhouette that brings the nostalgia of 1996 straight to the streets. These sneakers are a modern twist on a classic, combining historical significance with contemporary style. The sneaker integrates the cherished Space Jam colorway, traditionally seen on higher-cut models, onto the Jordan 11 Low for the first time, making it a groundbreaking release for collectors and new fans alike.

This rendition of the Jordan 11 Low features a sleek black upper composed of high-quality patent leather and ballistic mesh, perfectly complementing the Varsity Royal accents that can be found on the iconic Jumpman logo & portions of the outsole. Contrasted with a crisp white midsole and a translucent outsole, the design maintains the aesthetic integrity of the original high-top version. This shoe celebrates Michael Jordan's larger-than-life influence both on and off the court.

Released on May 18, 2024, at a retail price of $190, the 'Space Jam' Jordan 11 Retro Low is a piece of basketball heritage. As it hits the shelves, it brings with it stories of victories, cultural moments, and a legacy of innovation. Whether stepping out on the court or walking the streets, these sneakers offer a timeless style combined with unmatched comfort. Don’t miss out on owning a piece of history with the Jordan 11 Retro Low 'Space Jam', a must-have for sneaker enthusiasts around the globe.
